







       Basic groups of controls are used to organize groups of
       basic controls.  The following text describes the basic
       groups.

       PPPPaaaannnneeeellll            Organizes a collection of basic controls in
                        a horizontal, vertical, or 2-dimensional
                        layout.  A Panel is usually composed of
                        just one type of control.

       MMMMeeeennnnuuuu             Organizes a collection of buttons, labels,
                        and separators in a horizontal, vertical,
                        or 2-dimensional layout within a separate
                        Menu window.  There are three types of
                        Menus:  PullDown, Popup, and Option.  A
                        Menu is only available while it is popped
                        up or pulled down.

